<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="127" type="remarks">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="127">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="127">
Anthocodial rods are scarce in 
<taxonomicName authority="Lau &amp; Reimer, 2019" authorityName="Lau &amp; Reimer" authorityYear="2019" class="Anthozoa" family="Arulidae" genus="Bunga" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Bunga payung" order="Alcyonacea" pageId="0" pageNumber="127" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="species" species="payung">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="127">Bunga payung</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
gen. nov. et sp. nov. The 6-radiate type of sclerite was not observed in this genus but is present in 
<taxonomicName class="Anthozoa" family="Arulidae" genus="Arula" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Arula" order="Alcyonacea" pageId="0" pageNumber="127" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="127">Arula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName class="Anthozoa" family="Arulidae" genus="Hana" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Hana" order="Alcyonacea" pageId="0" pageNumber="127" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="127">Hana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the two other genera in the family 
<taxonomicName family="Arulidae" lsidName="" pageId="0" pageNumber="127" rank="family">Arulidae</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="127" type="etymology">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="127">Etymology.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="127">
From the Malaysian and Indonesian word 
<taxonomicName genus="Octocorallia" lsidName="Octocorallia payung" pageId="0" pageNumber="127" rank="species" species="payung">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="127">payung</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, which means umbrella; denoting the shape of the oral disc of the polyps, which resemble the shape of an umbrella.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
